description:
In lichen_lora_l2_init(), running is set to 0 while already holding the mutex:

```c
k_mutex_lock(&lora_mutex, K_FOREVER);

if (atomic_get(&lora_state.initialized)) {
    k_mutex_unlock(&lora_mutex);
    return 0;
}

lora_state.lora_dev = LORA_DEV;
atomic_set(&lora_state.running, 0);  // Line 302
atomic_set(&lora_state.aborted, 0);  // Line 303
```

This is not a bug - it's correct initialization. The atomic operations ensure proper memory ordering even though we hold the mutex. The mutex protects against concurrent init calls; the atomics ensure visibility to threads that might read without the mutex (like the TX fast path).

Closing - not a bug.
